That's your problem. The parent project also has a Vite dev server, and it's likely claiming port 5173 first.

The parent's [vite.config.ts](vite.config.ts) only proxies `/ws` — it has no `/api` proxy. So when you hit `localhost:5173/api/tags`, you're hitting the **parent's** Vite server, which has no idea about Ollama and just returns its `index.html` fallback.

**Fix:** Make sure the parent dev server isn't running when you start the scoring-sandbox one. If both need to run simultaneously, add an explicit port to the scoring-sandbox config:

```ts
server: {
  port: 5174,  // avoid colliding with the parent project
  proxy: { ... }
}
```

Or just kill the parent dev server, then `cd scoring-sandbox && bun run dev` — it'll get port 5173 and the proxy will work.
